<subSubSection pageId="89" pageNumber="90" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="89.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,510,536]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species was long thought to be rare and known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[1048,1096,511,537]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">type</typeStatus>
series off the 
<collectingRegion box="[1262,1365,510,536]" country="South Africa" name="Limpopo" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Limpopo</collectingRegion>
River estuary, but it has since been found to be quite common at depth throughout the Indo-West Pacific region from northern KZN, 
<collectingCountry box="[371,514,582,608]" name="South Africa" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">South Africa</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[549,613,583,609]" name="Japan" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Japan</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[768,874,582,608]" name="Australia" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Australia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
